div.p:
A. Government position is bifurcated one. On the one hand it offers free and
                    honest elections, while on other hand it steps up level of violence and
                    repression;

C. Parties of moderate opposition have tried to point up for GOES the road toward better relations and
                    acceptable electoral climate; in return they have been threatened by “Mano
                    Blanca”;

D. In Church meeting with parties of moderate opposition and enlightened elements
                    of private sector, agreement has been reached on five indispensable elements for
                    free election;
